org.jtrim.access

Class MultiAccessID<IDType1,IDType2>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jtrim.access.MultiAccessID<IDType1,IDType2>
  • Type Parameters:
    IDType1 - the type of the access ID of the first token
    IDType2 - the type of the access ID of the second token

    public final class MultiAccessID<IDType1,IDType2>
extends java.lang.Object
    Stores IDs of two AccessTokens. This class is used as an access ID by combined tokens.

    Thread safety

    Instances of this class are immutable and as such are thread-safe even in the face of unsynchronized concurrent access. Note that although instances are immutable, the IDs instances store might not necessarily immutable themselves. Note however that it is strongly recommended to use immutable access IDs.

    Synchronization transparency

    Methods of this class are synchronization transparent.
